Yo! Yo! Yo! Think you‚Äôve seen it all? 
 
Mars Blackmon thinks so. He‚Äôs witnessed every dunk, dime, Kid, King, and Know-It-All. Zimmie? She‚Äôs got other ideas.

Break barriers. Set records. Play through pain and never call it a comeback. 

Tiger is never done.

DEUCE. 
 
21. ADVANTAGE, NADAL.

The AntetokounBros Academy is more than basketball, it‚Äôs a space where kids from diverse backgrounds are given the chance to unleash and develop their potential through sport. Where everyone and anyone feels they belong. 

With the help of @onassis.stegi and @eurohoops_official, Giannis has created something that he never had growing up. A place where you‚Äôre encouraged to follow your passion and where having fun is as important as working hard. node.text: It‚Äôs just the start of something special. üí™ Congrats to @nellykorda on a brilliant performance on the course this weekend. Keep unlocking your greatness and pushing the game forward.

The @RTFKT X @nike Air Force 1 Forging Event kicks off on April 24th üëü‚öí. We are merging digital and physical worlds, collaborating with RTFKT and @takashipom to redeem virtual sneakers for iconic physical pairs. 

Oh, and If you‚Äôre in Shinjuku City, Tokyo, between 4/23-4/30, make sure to look up to see some epic 3D billboards. üëÄ

GET ‚ÄòEM BACK IN THE GAME üåç‚ôªÔ∏è
Get old gear back in the game with Move to Zero: Refresh, Rethink or Recycle.

Let‚Äôs take stock and then take new steps. Start with stuff that‚Äôs relegated to the past when it could be a player in our planet‚Äôs future. Let‚Äôs turn trash to treasure.

Comeback season is about to begin.

Hit up the link in our bio to find out more.

Support like never before.

Just like @salemmitchell, move with comfort and style for daysss in the Nike Flyknit Bra ü§∏
Ôøº
Swipe to see the fit and explore every way that movement helps you feel üíñ

Got old gear? It's been out of action too long. Benched and B-teamed. It's time to give it a second life. One that feels as exciting as the moment you first brought it home.

First up, rummage deep. Dig out beat up old festival kits or your favorite hoodie, the one with a hole in it.
Then choose your fighter:

REFRESH 'EM - clean and protect your old gear.
RETHINK 'EM - get creative and give old kicks and clothes a new identity.
RECYCLE 'EM - tap into Nike's Recycle + Donation service and give it a second life.

Join the #MoveToZeroChallenge and GET 'EM BACK IN THE GAME ‚ôªÔ∏è

Hit up the link in our bio to find out more üåç

The Mercurial XXV has taken flight. 25 years of unnatural speed. 

Celebrate with this iconic anniversary color way. ü¶Öüí®
#MERCXXV #nikefc

In Spring 2023, Nike brought together a collective of powerful, iconic women ‚Äî including elite athletes, collaborators, Nike trainers and partners in the world of dance, design, style and photography ‚Äî to celebrate the joy, possibility, freedom and boundless expression that can be found in all forms of movement.

The collective embodies togetherness, strength and attitude. They represent competitive sport, fitness, movement and style. They are soulful, united, and uninhibited.

In collaboration with an incredible creative community, elite athletes, and partners:
‚Ä®Photography by Renell Medrano @renellaice‚Ä®Styled by Gabriella Karefa-Johnson @gabriellak_j‚Ä®Cinematography by Charlie McHarg @appleshift4‚Ä®Organic Capture by Maya Spangler @stolenbesos

Old sole, new story. 

Introducing: The Our Force 1 collection, featuring digital renditions of AF1s past, present, and future built for the next generation. Nike‚Äôs first-ever virtual collection is inspired by the AF1 Low, a classic style that‚Äôs been remixed hundreds of times since it dropped in ‚Äò82. 

This is #OurForce1.

What happens when the lights go down at the Shop? You‚Äôd have to see it to believe it.

Too springy to stand still‚Äîthe Pegasus 40 is now available. ‚ú®

Baseball is in his blood. @ronaldacunajr13 is one of the brightest young stars in the game, and it‚Äôs his Venezuelan roots that have kept him grounded and motivated along the journey.

Now, in his first fully healthy season since 2021, he‚Äôs ready to take his game, his people and his sport to new heights.
Alex Roca, athlete with 76% physical disability and Cerebral palsy, is now a successful marathoner. He knows a thing or two about inspiring other athletes and leads by example. And he is never done.
